Authorities at Aitape in the West Sepik province on Papua New Guineas northwest coast said the tsunami that hit the coast west of Aitape on Friday night had wiped out three villages and had almost completely destroyed another
Authorities at Aitape in the West Sepik province on Papua New Guineas northwest coast said the tsunami that hit the coast west of the village on Friday night had wiped out three villages and had almost completely destroyed another
Authorities at Aitape in the West Sepik province on PNGs north-west coast said the tsunami that hit the coast west of Aitape on Friday night had wiped out three villages and had almost completely destroyed another according to an Australian Associated Press report sent Sunday from Aitape
